Taylor Rhodes Dickinson and Andrew Peter Cordeiro were married April 28 at the Church of the Good Shepherd in Lookout Mountain, Tenn. The Rev. Mac Brown, an Episcopal minister, performed the ceremony.
The couple met in Nashville at Vanderbilt University, from which they graduated. They each work at Goldman Sachs in New York, where the bride is an associate in the executive office and the groom is an associate in investment banking.
The bride, 26, is a daughter of Tennyson R. Dickinson and Thomas C. Dickinson of Lookout Mountain. The bride’s father is a commercial Realtor at Fletcher Bright in Chattanooga, Tenn. The bride’s mother is a director at Lake Winnepesaukah Amusement Park in Rossville, Ga.
The groom, 25, is the son of Carolyn R. Cordeiro and Dr. Peter G. Cordeiro of Westfield, N.J. The groom’s mother is a member of the board of the Society of Memorial Sloan Kettering. His father is a professor of surgery at Weill Cornell Medical College in New York and was the chief of plastic and reconstructive surgery at Memorial Sloan Kettering Cancer Center in New York.
